title: Grateful Dead Live at Wembley Arena on 1990-10-30
description: Jack Straw, Bertha, Wang Dang Doodle, Brown Eyed Women, Queen Jane Approximately, Row Jimmy, Let It Grow-> Jam-> Valley Road Picasso Moon, Foolish Heart, Looks Like Rain-> Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: Set 2 is a must have I've had an analog copie of this show for years, and it has long been one of my favorites.  One of the best Foolish Hearts I've ever heard, one of the best LL Rains ever, a great Terrapin Station,Then come out of Drums into a rockin wheel, Bobby lets it go during miracle Then a very emotional Black Peter followed by a hoppin lovelight.  They encore with a great version of The Weight.  On a 1-10 then high this underrated show gets a 10.

Europe '90 with Bruce!!! Im definately a fan of this tour along with the bustout of bruce's tunes. the let it grow>jam>valley road is spectacular, along with the second set. only problem is that it takes the first three or four songs in the first set to get the levels balanced.

jam>Valley Road SSWWWWWWEEEEETTTTTT!!

Only regret is not being there.

Download ASAP!

Great sound so there should be no arguement.

"As good as it gets" I don`t know if its because I was there but to
me it`s As good as it gets!Once they get over initial sound problems the sound comes to life.
From Queen Jane to Valley Road from the first
set the sound is spot on.The second set is a must
listen,overall top marks for this gig.Download now!!

we'd waited 9 years How would you feel Like a pack wolves we carefully  arrived. We were not disappointed. Oh to be drenched in their sound again after those 9 long years. We danced ourselves silly that second set getting ready for the next night. Great start to the 3 night run

2 WORDS.................. download this show and tomorrows ASAP..crisp sound, great energy, and just seems like the band ws having a good old time......oh to be young and in London 15 years ago......thanx again internet archive..you keep us truckin'!!!!
nice!! queen jane and on, real nice sound, wish i had the chance to go to europe in 90'! have friends that did (jerks)just kidding, download this one!

Brings It All Back This was my first and only time i ever got to see the dead live. After a 7 hour bus journey and the maze of london's tube system , we arrived at wembley. Unfortunatley our seats were right at the back left so first interval we got into the main arena and everything changed !! Maybe it was the acid i had scored?! or the mushrooms that i'd taken before the acid but during " Looks Like Rain " , believe me it was raining !!!
This was the greatest concert i have ever attended . I saw the Dead , saw God and smiled all the way home..

Dust it off IMO, the finest of the three London shows. Worst songlist- best playing. 

I'll skip the song by song review, just play this puppie.

PS- The pink floyd phone calls during space are cool.

whoosh This was the fourth time I'd seen the Dead. I remember distinctly the rush of emotion when they struck up Jack Straw. Couldn't leap about up front as we had our one year old with us. She fell asleep after twenty minutes, but now she can hear what she missed!

I was there I was at 4 Shows that tour- 10-30 & 31 London and 10-27 & 28 Paris- It never ceases to amaze me how different the shows are from the "tape" and being there- I distinctly remember the Halloween show (10-31) being EXPLOSIVE and this show being awful as the sound mix was never right the entire show- In fact- the reason the piano lead in to Valley road is interesting is because Bruce Hornsby didn't want the Band to exit after such an awful first set- almost like they couldn't wait to get off the stage- whereas Bruce wasn't about to let it end on without at least one good song ! While playing with the Audience on the classical lead in- the stage went dark with Jerry and Bobby looking at Bruce  with a "what are you doing look on their face" - the 2nd set not much better! 

I left hoping for what came true the next  night- - yet this Board is awesome- well balanced and well played- and the Lovelight at the end smokes- 

"Just goes to show - you never know ....." !!!

Ridiculous This show is ridiculous.

So good it should be banned in Britain.

No, don't wanna go there.

Anyway, this is a great recording of a great performance.
old valley road beautiful jam into valley road...love it.  song 8-9

Uncle Jon's Band I was gifted a bunch of early Dead albums in 1984 by my Uncle Jon at just the right age, 17 - I'd been smoking Sweet Mary Jane and dropping acid for a year thanks to my best mate! 

This was the only UK Dead tour that happened after this gift, miracle as it happened to be - so me, my best mate and his bird went down to dirty old London Town to see the Dead at Wemberley. Sitting left of stage, but great view, the moment the band came on stage that familiar sweet aroma filled the arena and we were offered a few tokes from our Deadhead neighbours to help us on our way. The greatest gift to us on that night was Terrapin / Space / Wheel, we'd been playin' and lovin' these tunes almost to death. The quality in this recording mirrors my memory of this evening, the only time I saw Jerry and the band in person. This comes a week after Bob Hunter passed, so emotions are high, but this must rank as one of the highlights of my life. I'm honoured as an Englishman to say I've seen the Dead, and what a show! Thank you, Uncle Jon xxx
